<h1><strong>Program Mission &amp; What We Do</strong></h1>
<hr />
<p><strong><span style="color: #303538; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">OUR MISSION:</span></strong><span style="color: #303538; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">&nbsp;to help </span><em style="color: #303538; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">foreign Pathway students</em><span style="color: #303538; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;"> develop their English skills, through realtime interaction with </span><em style="color: #303538; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">native-level English speakers</em><span style="color: #303538; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">.</span><strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>HOW IT WORKS:</strong> our office facilitates matches of <em>Pathway students</em> with registered <em>volunteers</em>; speaking partnerships last for <em>one semester</em>, and 20-40 minute visits are held <em>twice a week</em> through <a href="http://www.skype.com/" target="_blank">Skype</a>. The students earn <span style="text-decoration: underline;">2 credits</span> for each of the 3 semesters they participate as an <strong>E</strong>nglish <strong>L</strong>anguage <strong>L</strong>earner.</p>
<p><strong>WHAT IS DISCUSSED:</strong> identical discussion material is provided to the student and volunteer that correlates with the student's online coursework.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>WHAT ELSE?</strong> Depending on who you are, the following pages/videos will answer your questions: <br />[<a href="x69374.xml">Pathway Student</a>], [<a href="x69375.xml">Volunteering</a>], [<a href="x69376.xml">Pathway Missionary/Instructor</a>]</p>
